<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving width for block-level non-replaced elements in normal flow when both right and left margins are auto</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When both left and right margins are auto, the used values become equal." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
            #d1
            {
                background: green;
                width: 200px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                margin: 0 auto;
                padding: 0 0;
                width: 100px;
                border-width: 0 0;
                border-color: black;
                border-style: solid;
                background-color: white;
                height: 20px;
            }
            #d3
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 20px;
                left: 0;
                width: 50px;
                height: 20px;
                background: black;
            }
            #d4
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 20px;
                left: 150px;
                width: 50px;
                height: 20px;
                background: black;
            }
            p
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 60px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2"></div>
        </div>
        <div id="d3"></div>
        <div id="d4"></div>
        <p>Test passes if the width of the green boxes match the black boxes.</p>
    </body>
</html>